Thanks hummeline and lifeasdaddy, every little bit helps! Here is a link to a <a href="http://www.visit.heritage.nsw.gov.au/16_subnav_09_2.cfm?item_id=&amp;itemid=5045515&amp;sort_by=&amp;item_name=&amp;suburb_name=&amp;product_category=&amp;state_theme=&amp;product_region=8" rel="nofollow">history of Audley at the Heritage Council of NSW</a>

To quote: &quot;Between 1891 and 1893 the focus was on making the park visitor-friendly...The accommodation was first known as the public pavilion, then 'The Rest' and for most of its history as 'Allambie House'. In 1893 the first guide book was published.&quot;

And further down: &quot;In 1973 Allambie House kiosk and the swimming pool kiosk were demolished. Two years later Allambie House its self was burnt to the ground.&quot;
